  "description": "IACKD is a multimodal neurophysiological dataset combining electroencephalography (EEG) recordings with hand kinematics data collected during a task designed to investigate intention-action conflict. The dataset comprises raw EEG signals and synchronized kinematic measurements from participants performing motor tasks, providing a resource for studying the neural mechanisms underlying motor planning and conflict resolution.",
